title: One Commonplace Day
creator: Pansy aka  Isabella Alden
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of One Commonplace Day, by Pansy. Read by TriciaG. A temperance lecturer misses his train and ends up attending a town picnic. It was a common enough picnic on a commonplace day. But the discussions, actions, and attitudes from that picnic reverberate through the lives of many people. What are the far-reaching consequences of one commonplace day in OUR lives?
